article.headline: Rider 83, Siena 72
article.story: LAWRENCEVILLE, N.J. -- Jeff Jones scores 18 points, including five 3-pointers, to pace five in double figures for Rider in an 83-72 win over Siena Sunday. Anthony Myles added 13 points, Brandon Penn 12, Novar Gadson 11 and Junior Fortunat 10 for the Broncs (9-14, 6-5 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Rider has matched its season high with three straight wins, and avenged a Jan. 12 loss at Siena. In a back-and-forth game, Penn hit a 3 to put the Broncs up 35-27 at halftime. But the Saints stormed back after intermission, as Evan Hymes hit a trio of 3-pointers to help fuel a 23-10 run for a 15-point lead with about 13 minutes left. Down 57-56 with 8 1/2 minutes to play, Jones hit a pair of 3-pointers as Rider put together a 13-4 run to win it. O.D. Anosike scored 22 point and grabbed 16 rebounds to lead Siena (10-11, 5-6).
